 Six people were arrested for their involvement in looting that took place at various foreign-owned shops in Witbank on Wednesday. Watch. In a video, a shop owner can be seen fighting back while looters steal items like speakers and fans. According to police spokesperson Brigadier Leonard Hlathi, several stolen items were recovered. "Police stations have been given a strict mandate to conduct intensive visible patrols in all areas but also prioritise and monitor the areas with a large number of foreign-owned shops," he said in a statement. Mpumalanga police commissioner Lieutenant General Bethuel Mondli Zuma condemned the "act of criminality". "General Zuma urges people to act responsibly and obey the law at all times," Hlathi said. The suspects are expected to appear in the Witbank Magistrate's Court on Friday on charges of the possession of stolen property, theft as well as assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm. 